The Liberty Mutual policy provides secondary coverage for third-party liability. For trips for cars registered in Maryland the policy provides primary coverage. All plans come standard with at least state minimum liability coverage. The policy is arranged through Turo Insurance Agency, a licensed insurance provider. For terms, conditions, and exclusions, visit the Turo Insurance Agency section at support.turo.com. Turo is not an insurance company, and the contractual allocation of responsibility for physical damage to the host’s vehicle is not insurance.
Encourage guests to book longer trips by offering discounts for weekend, weekly and monthly trips.

If you decline Turo protection, you are required to provide commercial insurance and will be characterized as a Commercial Host.
Commercial Hosts are independent car rental companies and entrepreneurs who can provide their own commercial rental insurance to protect their cars and their guests during trips booked on Turo.
As a Commercial Host, you must provide the minimum insurance (liability and/or physical damage) mandated by applicable law directly to your guests to cover all of your vehicles. You choose to waive all protection, coverages, and roadside assistance offered via Turo.
We may review your insurance for eligibility, but don’t have the obligation to do so. If we have concerns, we will restrict your vehicles from the Turo marketplace.
I agree to the additional terms and recognize that I am exclusively responsible for providing rental insurance coverage for any rental transaction of my vehicles through Turo.
